<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="94.[151,1437,330,1005]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[266,486,690,718]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref367399" refString="Rondani, C. (1845 b) Genera italica Conopidarum distincta et descripta. Fragmentum decimum tertium ad inserviendum dipterologiae italicae. Magasin de Zoologie d'Anatomie Comparee et de Palaeontologie, Series 2, 153, 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1845">Rondani (1845b: 6)</bibRefCitation>
described both sexes of 
<taxonomicName box="[761,1021,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Leopoldius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diadematus">
<emphasis box="[761,1021,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Leopoldius diadematus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without specifying the exact 
<taxonomicName box="[1351,1437,691,717]" family="Number" pageId="94" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
of specimens: “ 
<emphasis box="[373,677,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">marem et foeminam collegi</emphasis>
[I collected the male and the female]”. In his redescription 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." pageId="94" pageNumber="95" refId="ref368401" refString="Rondani, C. (1857) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: II. Species italicae ordinis dipterorum in genera characteribus definita, ordinatim collectae, methodo analitica distinctae, et novis vel minus cognitis descriptis. Pars prima. Oestridae: Syrphfidae [sic!]: Conopidae. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 264 pp., 1 pl. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8160" type="book" year="1857">Rondani (1857: 221)</bibRefCitation>
specified having described the species on a single male and a single female: “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
quando speciem hanc evulgavi, duo tantum ejusdem exemplaria a me observata fuerunt, 
<taxonomicName box="[1004,1118,799,825]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Etruria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="masculum">masculum</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[1124,1186,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Individum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unum">unum</taxonomicName>
et alterum foemineum
</emphasis>
[When I described this species I observed only 
<specimenCount box="[748,918,835,861]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
, first 
<specimenCount box="[986,1090,835,861]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
and later 
<specimenCount box="[1208,1343,834,861]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
]”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Stuke, J. - H." pageId="94" pageNumber="95" refId="ref376050" refString="Stuke, J. - H. (2017) World catalogue of insects. Volume 15. Conopidae (Dipter a). Brill, Leiden, 354 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004271845" type="book" year="2017">Stuke (2017: 58)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<specimenCount box="[426,544,871,897]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="male">three male</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[553,651,871,897]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">syntypes</typeStatus>
and 
<specimenCount box="[707,831,871,897]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[839,926,871,897]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">syntype</typeStatus>
in the MZUF. There are 
<specimenCount box="[1211,1339,871,897]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="male">three males</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
in the MZUF and 
<specimenCount box="[486,622,907,933]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
in the OUMNH: these specimens did not have any label indicating their type status. We are unable to single out the 
<specimenCount box="[679,844,943,969]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
upon which Rondani based his description. We leave the recognition of the 
<specimenCount box="[446,593,979,1005]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">two syntypes</specimenCount>
to a future specialist.
</paragraph>
